
"If either of y'all start an argument in this car I will take your phones away and play Nickelback for the rest of the trip," My father warned, giving us a stern look. Considering the bags under his eyes, we probably cut his beauty sleep short this morning. I would make a joke about it if he wasn't so bitter over it.
"Okay, Dad." Hannah and I looked at each other with wide eyes. The trip was only thirty minutes long but there was no way we were suffering through a Nickelback album. We could get along for this trip to save our ears from that torture.